			{\sl Django Developer,} Potato London \hfill
                        January 2012 - August 2012 \\
			\hrule
			Freelance work for Google including architectural design, user experience studies and development with Python, Appengine, Django-nonrel, jQuery \& CSS.
			
{\sl Google Engage} \\
Engage\footnote{\myurl{http://www.google.com/ads/engage/index.html}} is Google's largest single contributor of marketing revenue, taking the form of a multi-level coupon distribution system spanning 61 countries and 27 languages. I worked as part of a dedicated team of 8 full-time developers working across all areas of features, maintenance and support of the system. My work included the initial designs for a CloudSQL mirror for the Appengine datastore that optimised specific query times by a factor of 30, UX redesign of the admin CMS form entry system, refactoring low level caching middleware and feature design across many areas of the site.   
			
{\sl Google Campus London} \\
Led the design and development of social features for Google's startup incubator, Campus London\footnote{\myurl{http://www.campuslondon.com}}. My work included building custom multiple social authentication, user \& event management, and an  API for social profile integrated card access to the caf\'{e}.

{\sl Google Fiber} \\
Lead developer in delivering our in-house events management system and CMS for a 50+ person events team for Google Fiber\footnote{\myurl{http://www.google.com/fiber/kansascity/index.html}} to manage the forthcoming launch of 1Gbps fibre optic broadband in Kansas City. 

{\sl Web Solutions Engineer,} Xim Ltd. \hfill October 2012 - August 2013 \\
			\hrule
                        Deigned and implemented the core systems for
                        the GoldUI\footnote{\myurl{http://www.goldui.eu/}}
                        European AAL Project for Adaptive embedded
                        human interfaces designed for older people.
                        

My tasks involved working with both SQL and NoSQL databases and
building a Backbone.js mobile application that utilises responsive design
principles so as to be used on a smart phone, android bed side radio
device, tablet or television. The application structure was made
highly modular and pluggable to facilitate adding future services.

By modifying the open source Python,
Flask\footnote{\myurl{http://flask.pocoo.org/}} based
foAuth\footnote{\myurl{https://github.com/foauth/foauth.org}} project to work
with our databases and Backbone app I built
an authentication system that can scale and can be used to
authenticate and authorise oAuth services by both carers
on the web interfaces or by the end users on mobile devices.

My work also included making a social news feed service pulling information
from facebook and a news feed parser that allows a carer to select from
Tiscali's rss feeds on the web interface and the end user to read
these from their mobile device.

{\sl CTO,} Doolally Concepts Ltd. \hfill January 2013 - August 2013 \\ \hrule
Worked with Dr. Raj Persaud, a consultant psychiatrist, broadcaster and author of popular books about psychiatry, to develop and implement his concept of an
iPhone app that uses film taste to give feedback on compatibility and
relationship advice. The app uses trailers that are selected based on
genre and matches users based on psychological research in the area of
aesthetic preferences. 

 {\sl Responsibilities}
             
             \begin{itemize}  \itemsep -2pt %reduce space between items
                   \item Built the API backend in Django
		\item Designed, from research, the compatibility algorithms
		\item Built a psychological testing site to validate these algorithms (with third party academic review from Dr. Viren Swami at the University of Westminster)
		\item Facebook integration
		\item Apple Push Notifications
		\item Hiring and managing iOS developers
		\item Mobile Testing using TestFlight
		\item Email notifications
		\item Help video script editorial, filming, processing and hosting
		\item Film trailer API consumption and processing
		\item Admin interface for genre assignment, quotes \& film selection (for minigame)
		\item 90\% test coverage
 \end{itemize}
        
